assignName(string).details: Calls the storage contract and assigns the name for the msg.sender.

params.name: Name to add a name record for.

params.addr: Address to find the min limit for.

isOwner().return: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

renounceStorageOwnership().details: Renounces the storage owner.      Renouncing the owner will render the storage contract useless.      ONLY FOR PURPOSES OF SELF-DESTRUCTING THE CONTRACT!

params.name: Name to resolve to an address.

setMinLimit(address,uint8).details: Sets the name min limit for a given address.

params.addr: Address to set the limit on.
params.minLimit: Minimum length of any future added name records.

setMinLimit(address,uint8).return: True if setting the limit succeeds.

setStorageAddress(address).details: Sets the storage address and enables all other functions.      All other functions rely on a valid storage contract address      so this function needs to be called first.

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

transferStorageOwnership(address).details: Changes the storage owner.      Changing it will remove the permissions from this contract.       The new owner should be another ANS contract.      ONLY FOR PURPOSES OF UPGRADING THE ANS CONTRACT!

params.newOwner: New owner of the storage contract.

renounceOwnership().notice: Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.
